堆美国债券，主要是通过其中央银行。中央银行持有的外币债券称为“外汇储备”、“外汇储备”或简称“储备”。当我们说世界上大多数“储备”都是“美元”，或者说美元是“储备货币”时，我们的意思是，各国央行持有的大部分外币债券都是美国债券。在这种情况下，“大多数”实际上意味着 60% 左右： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg" width="1308" height="546" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:546,&quot;width&quot;:1308,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:107446,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F84ec93bc-98b4-4e37-94cf-a8ebae4311af_1308x546.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://data.imf.org/?sk=e6a5f467-c14b-4aa8-9f6d-5a09ec4e62a4">国际货币基金组织</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>因此，世界各地对美国债券的需求很大。但要购买这些债券，购买储备的国家必须将本国货币兑换成美元。这使得美元更加昂贵，而其他国家的货币更加便宜。这使得这些国家的商品和服务出口更具竞争力，而美国的出口竞争力下降。换句话说，<em>对美国债券的需求挤出了对美国商品和服务的需求</em>。</p><p>这让美国制造商和可贸易服务提供商的日子变得更加艰难，因为这降低了他们的竞争力。它使<em>廉价进口产品</em>——尤其是廉价的中国进口产品——变得更加便宜，这使得工厂很难留在美国，而由此导致的美国制造业衰退削弱了我们军队在发生重大战争时生产大量武器的能力。</p><p>但与此同时，“坚挺”的美元使美国人更容易买得起廉价的进口商品，从而让他们消费更多。而且许多经济学家还认为，它降低了美国的利率，使美国人更容易借钱。<em>轻松借贷</em>可以刺激消费（至少在短期内），也能提振依赖大量借贷才能运营的金融业。最后，这使得美国政府更容易对其他国家实施金融制裁，就像我们对俄罗斯和伊朗所做的那样。</p><p>因此，“强势”美元有赢家和输家。这就是为什么我不喜欢这里的“强势”这个词——昂贵的美元会让美国消费者和金融家以及制裁变得更强，但它会让出口商、制造商和军队变得更弱。</p><p>现在，有两件我们实际上<em>不</em>知道的重要事情：</p><ol><li><p>我们不知道<em>为什么</em>所有这些国家都想要所有这些美国债券。</p></li><li><p>我们不知道美国的贸易逆差<em>有多少</em>是由海外对美国债券的需求造成的。</p></li></ol><p>关于各国央行为何希望持有美国债券的原因有多种理论，而且所有这些理论都可能同时成立。一种理论认为，其他国家购买美国债券是为了<em>故意保持本国货币便宜</em>，这样他们就可以出口更多的东西，因为他们认为出口更多的东西从长远来看将有助于他们的经济。另一种理论是，这些美国债券充当了抵御<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-sri-lanka-is-having-an-economic">货币危机</a><em>的一种保险</em>——如果你的货币贬值太多，以至于你无力承担食品和燃料的进口，你可以出售部分美元储备来支撑你的货币价值。第三种理论是，由于美元经常<em>用于贸易和国际金融</em>，其他国家希望保留一些美国债券，以便可以将其出售换成美元以购买进口产品。还有一些其他的理论。</p><p>无论出于何种原因，国际上对美国债券的强劲需求很可能导致美元相对于其他货币更加昂贵。贵了<em>多少</em>，我们不知道。但如果你想减少美国的贸易赤字和/或提高美国出口在世界市场上的竞争力——这是两个不同但相关的目标——那么美元作为“储备货币”的角色就是你前进道路上的一大障碍。只要大量外国央行购买美国债券，美元就永远是一种昂贵的货币，这使得向海外出售更多美国产品或平衡贸易平衡成为一场艰苦的战斗。</p><p>这就是为什么Robert Lighthizer非常关心贸易赤字的原因， <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/04/15/devaluing-dollar-trump-trade-war-00152009#:~:text=Advisers%20close%20to%20the%20former,exports%20but%20also%20fuel%20inflation.">他想贬值美元</a>。这也是为什么任何关心保护和扩大美国工业能力的人——现在包括许多进步派<em>和</em>许多保守派——都不可避免地必须考虑美元的价值。</p><h4>美元贬值在实践中会如何运作？</h4><p>如果您希望货币变得更便宜，您可以做一些基本的事情。这些包括：</p><ol><li><p>让央行印钞（降低利率）</p></li><li><p>让美国人增加储蓄</p></li><li><p>让央行购买外币（货币干预）</p></li><li><p>向外国施压，要求其货币兑美元升值</p></li><li><p>限制外国人购买美国债券（资本管制）</p></li></ol><p> Menzie Chinn 有<a href="https://econbrowser.com/archives/2024/05/hi-ho-hi-ho-its-off-to-fx-war-we-go">一篇很棒的博客文章</a>，他在其中讨论了此列表中的选项 (1)、(3) 和 (4)，并包含一些有用的研究论文以供参考。不管怎样，让我们​​来看看这些选项并列出它们的优点和缺点。</p><h5><strong>印钞/降低利率</strong></h5><p>首先，请记住，外汇市场上美元的价值是由美元的供需决定的。我讲的都是需求方，但供给方也很重要。如果您增加了世界上美元的供应，那应该推动美元价格（即汇率）下降。因此，美联储可以打印一堆钱，以贬值美元。这将降低利率，这将使我们的债券在财务上达成更糟糕的交易。据推测，这将使一些国家购买更少的美国债券，从而贬值美元。</p><p>有几个问题。首先，打印一堆钱会导致一堆通货膨胀，美国人已经很生气了。其次，我们关心的主要贸易赤字是与中国的贸易赤字，我们最关心与中国竞争的国家的出口是中国。实际上，如果您将欧盟视为一个国家，几乎所有世界上的贸易失衡都只是美国贸易赤字与中国贸易盈余相匹配： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg" width="1422" height="1033" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/df670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1033,&quot;width&quot;:1422,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:267908,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fdf670593-f20c-47b2-ae9e-c742d33f4038_1422x1033.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://x.com/Brad_Setser/status/1762614544520851918">Brad Setser</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>中国的中央银行可能关心的是财务收益和损失要比欧洲，亚洲等美国盟国盟军少得多。因此，印刷资金可能不会有效地降低美中 - 中国的贸易赤字，这只会影响我们与韩国，台湾和德国等国家的赤字要小得多，削弱了这些盟友的出口竞争力，而对中国则没有太大的作用。</p><p>因此，导致美国的通货膨胀并没有为改变美国/中国的贸易平衡而做太多事情听起来并不是一个好主意。毫不奇怪，我看不到有人在暗示这一点。</p><h5>让美国人增加储蓄</h5><p>第二个想法 - 哪个没有提及，但是哪个迈尔斯·金博尔（Miles Kimball）教我您在这篇博客文章中阅读的内容的2/3，以为我们应该做 - 是为了让美国人节省更多的钱。如果美国家庭和美国公司购买了更多的美国债券，那将使它们更昂贵（即它将降低利率）。这将以不会导致通货膨胀的方式这样做，因为当美国人节省更多时，这意味着他们消耗较少，因此总需求会下降。</p><p>目前，<a href="https://worldpopulationreview.com/country-rankings/savings-rate-by-country">与许多其他国家（尤其是中国）相比，</a>美国节省了太多。我们也许可以使用策略来提高这一数量。问题是“如何？”。多年来，经济学家认为，诸如401K和其他事情的税收减税和税收抵免之类的政策将使美国人节省更多。但是，如果他们这样做了，那肯定不会显示在总统计数据中。这些年来，个人储蓄率大部分都下降了： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png" width="1318" height="450" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:450,&quot;width&quot;:1318,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:66331,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb07151ba-d434-409f-9e34-3779c552c53f_1318x450.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>公司储蓄率也没有太大变化。因此，目前尚不清楚如何让美国节省更多的钱。一种选择是深度财政紧缩，但这在政治上很艰难，尤其是在您必须做的规模上以影响汇率。</p><p>最重要的是，如果中国的中央银行非常关心它所获得的美国债券的利率，那么节省更多的东西，例如打印资金，才会减少我们对中国的赤字。它可能<em>不在乎</em>。因此，储蓄诱因可能是一项非常昂贵的政策，因为在汇率变化方面没有很多收益。</p><h5>消毒货币干预</h5><p>第三种选择是让美联储印刷资金并用它购买中国资产 - 元负有债券，中国股票，房地产等。这称为货币干预或外汇干预。这就是中国对我们所做的事情 - 这是他们首先积累所有这些美元储备的方式。我们可以立即回到他们身边。</p><p>如果美联储只是在没有其他任何事情的情况下做到这一点，那将降低利率并导致美元供应量大幅增加，这将增加通货膨胀的风险，如上所述。这就是所谓的“未经证实的干预措施”。但是，如果美联储同时购买了中国资产的同时出售美国债券，那么对通货膨胀和利率的影响将取消。这就是所谓的“消毒干预措施”。</p><p>门齐·钦（Menzie Chinn）<a href="https://econbrowser.com/archives/2024/05/hi-ho-hi-ho-its-off-to-fx-war-we-go">写道</a>：“没有太多证据表明，对于拥有开放资本市场的国家，这在扩展的基础上有效，”并将我们送往<a href="https://users.ssc.wisc.edu/~mchinn/Popper_FXI_apr22.pdf">Popper（2022）的文献调查</a>。但是Popper并没有真正结论任何一种结论 - 获得这样的宏观物质的令人信服的经验证据本质上很难，因为没有真正的方法可以隔离因果关系。因此，我认为我们真的不知道这是否会起作用，并且有<a href="https://www.imf.org/en/Publications/WP/Issues/2020/07/07/A-Conceptual-Model-for-the-Integrated-Policy-Framework-49558">一些理论表明这可能是有效的</a>。但是未知数很大。</p><p>无论如何，我认为灭菌干预措施是列表中最有前途的政策工具，这是我们应该研究的一种。这将需要一些法律上的更改，既要允许美联储这样做，又要做到这一点。但是，通货膨胀的低风险以及我们可以将政策专门针对中国的事实，使其成为一个非常有吸引力的选择。</p><h5>向其他国家施加压力以贬值其货币</h5><p>但是无论如何，让我们继续谈论罗伯特·莱特希泽（Robert Lighthizer）实际上似乎想到了什么 - 迫使外国政府贬低其货币。基本上，这意味着我们将与其他国家坐在一个房间里，并说：“好的，您需要停止购买这么多的美国债券。实际上，卖掉了您拥有的货币，直到您的货币相对于美元越来越昂贵。”</p><p>实际上，我们以前在1985年做过一次。它被称为<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plaza_Accord">广场协议</a>。我们成功地向欧洲盟友和日本施加了压力，以欣赏他们相对于美元的货币，而美元实际上确实变得“弱”。尽管<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plaza_Accord#Objective_failure">人们辩论</a>它的有效性，但普遍的共识是，广场在很大程度上成功地<a href="https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/countries/USA/united-states/trade-balance-deficit#google_vignette">减少了1980年代的美国贸易赤字</a>。 <a class="footnote-anchor" data-component-name="FootnoteAnchorToDOM" id="footnote-anchor-2" href="#footnote-2" target="_self">2</a></p><p>因此，这实际上将是一个非常有前途的途径，即使不是一个大问题，就可以安全地贬值美元：唯一真正重要的贸易伙伴，即中国，不像1985年美国的盟友那样<em>同意这一点</em>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2019/05/23/as-the-trade-war-heats-up-china-looks-to-japans-past-for-lessons">据报道，中国领导人认为</a>，广场协定是日本经济的脱轨，并导致了数十年的停滞。这可能是错误的 - 实际上，广场协议完全<em>未能</em>减少美国与日本的双边贸易赤字。所有减少贸易赤字都来自欧洲。但是中国的领导人<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-is-china-producing-so-many-export">似乎认为</a>，巨大的贸易盈余符合他们的国家利益，并且欣赏他们的货币将代表在美国压力下屈服，因此他们只是<a href="http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-08/31/c_137433229.htm">不会这样做</a>。</p><p>这意味着，正如Lighthizer似乎正在计划的那样，“广场协议2.0”将完全针对美国的亚洲和欧洲盟友，他们与美国的贸易过剩很小。如果日本，台湾，韩国等都赞赏他们的货币，而中国则没有，那将只是损害美国的盟友并加强中国。这可能算是罗伯特·莱特（Robert Lighthizer）的“胜利”，但实际上，这对美国来说将是损失</p><h5>资本控制</h5><p>我还可以提到一个选择，即使这不太可能发生。到目前为止，我到目前为止所谈论的一切都是正确的，在一个<em>自由资本流动</em>的世界中 - 换句话说，它假设有一个“外汇市场”，您可以在这里换日元，日元，卢比，卢比卢比，欧元卢比等等在。但是一些国家限制其公民及其公司买卖外币。这些限制称为“资本控制”。中国有资本管制，但目前美国没有。</p><p>美国可以制定资本管制，结束自1973年以来一直盛行的浮动汇率和更多或不再使用的自由资本运输系统。我们可以制定一项法律，限制外国购买美国债券的购买，或对这些购买征税。我见过的唯一的人建议这是<a href="https://carnegieendowment.org/china-financial-markets/2024/02/can-trade-intervention-lead-to-freer-trade?lang=en">迈克尔·佩蒂斯（Michael Pettis）</a> ：</p><blockquote><p> [a]更直接，更集中的关税替代品是资本控制。如果美国要征税资本流入，或者以其他方式限制了盈余经济体的资本流入，那么美国贸易帐户及其国内储蓄率就无需适应外国流入净流入。也不需要进口关税。</p></blockquote><p>这将有效，尽管要实施需要大量时间和精力。这将导致我们的整个经济和金融体系的改变。</p><p> And in the end, there&#39;s no guarantee that it would reduce our bilateral trade deficit with China — the entire brunt of the adjustment might fall on US allies, who might be forced to run trade <em>deficits</em> against the US in order to balance out China&#39;s trade surplus 。 This is especially likely because China&#39;s government would be by far the most willing — and able — to pay the tax for buying US bonds. So it would likely keep buying bonds, while other countries would be forced to stop.</p><p> If reducing the US&#39; overall trade deficit is your overriding goal, that counts as a “win”. But if your goal is to strengthen the export industries of the US-led geopolitical bloc relative to China, that would not be a good outcome.</p><h4> General costs and risks of dollar devaluation</h4><p> So of all the options on the table, sterilized intervention — having the Fed buy Chinese assets and sell US bonds — seems like the best. Unfortunately, no one is talking about it. And all the other options seem much more likely to punch down on America&#39;s allies, whose economies are already much weaker than our own, while doing relatively little to address the central problem of the bilateral deficit with China.</p><p> Also, it&#39;s worth mentioning that any policy to devalue the dollar would inevitably come with some costs and risks. For one thing, dollar devaluation would make imports more expensive for Americans. Another way of putting this is that the US&#39; trade deficit allows it to increase consumption — not by a huge amount, maybe only 4%, but enough to notice.</p><p> More importantly, dollar devaluation could put a lot of strain on the American financial system. It&#39;s not just foreign governments who hold US bonds — in fact, most of those bonds are held domestically, especially by US banks. Devaluing the dollar would lead to lower demand for US bonds, which could drop their price by a little or a lot. This might not be a big danger — in 2015, China <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/view/articles/2016-02-29/capital-flight-delivers-a-verdict-on-china-s-economy?sref=R8NfLgwS">sold off a substantial portion</a> of its dollar reserves, and the value of US bonds didn&#39;t really shift (in econ jargon, total demand turned out to be highly inelastic). But if this time turned out differently, it could hurt the balance sheets of many US banks — recall that a decrease in the value of government bonds <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/why-was-there-a-run-on-silicon-valley">almost caused a banking crisis</a> back in 2023.</p><p> These costs and risks are why, frankly, I don&#39;t expect Trump to actually implement any of Lighthizer&#39;s proposals. Trump would be afraid that anything that caused inflation would lose him popular support. And because he built his own fortune on cheap loans, he&#39;s unlikely to embrace any policy that would cut off major sources of cheap loans from abroad. Also, the TikTok affair showed that Trump is <a href="https://time.com/6900348/tiktok-ban-donald-trump-congress/">easily pressured</a> by China and its proxies.</p><p> But if Biden wins, or if someone else serious gets into office, I would take a look at sterilized currency intervention as a way to nudge China toward appreciating its currency.</p><p>谁知道呢？ A nudge might be all it takes. My analysis above was predicated on the idea that China&#39;s leaders don&#39;t <em>want</em> to appreciate the yuan. China&#39;s leaders basically don&#39;t do anything they don&#39;t want to do. But they might <em>change their mind</em> about what&#39;s in their own best interests.</p><p> In fact, their mind might already be in the process of changing. The US financial sanctions on Russia have motivated China to start <a href="https://www.wsj.com/finance/currencies/chinas-yuan-is-quietly-gaining-ground-f0b8994b">using more yuan in its foreign trade</a> and fewer dollars, in order to reduce its own vulnerability to a similar attack. That effort is still in its infancy, but if it continues, it&#39;ll reduce Chinese demand for dollars somewhat. Meanwhile, China is buying up <a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/04/08/gold-record-highs">massive amounts of gold</a> , signaling its shift away from US bonds as the core of its reserves. It may even be <a href="https://www.reuters.com/markets/asia/chinas-us-bond-shifts-put-dollar-under-geopolitical-spotlight-2024-05-21/">selling down some</a> of its US bond holdings, though it&#39;s hard to tell; it might just be having its state-owned banks <a href="https://www.cfr.org/blog/chinas-new-currency-playbook">buy more to compensate</a> .</p><p> But in any case, these are signs that China&#39;s leaders are growing less content with a global financial order in which they depend on the hegemony of the US dollar. A nudge, in terms of a well-timed currency intervention by the US government — or even a few more <a href="https://www.wsj.com/politics/national-security/u-s-takes-aim-at-chinese-banks-aiding-russia-war-effort-fcf76dcc">well-placed financial sanctions</a> on Chinse companies that supply Russia&#39;s war effort — might help accelerate this shift in their thinking. </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollar?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-to-devalue-the-dollar?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"><a id="footnote-1" href="#footnote-anchor-1" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">1</a><div class="footnote-content"><p> A portion of this trade deficit is fake, for two reasons. First, US companies <a href="https://www.cbo.gov/system/files/2019-05/55284-Transfer%20Pricing-WP.pdf">pretend that they make their profits overseas</a> , in order to avoid taxes. Second, the trade deficit doesn&#39;t take value-added trade into account — it only measures where things were assembled, not where the value of their components and designs was created. But even netting out those two things, the US trade deficit is still quite large.</p></div></div><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"> <a id="footnote-2" href="#footnote-anchor-2" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">2</a><div class="footnote-content"><p> In fact, it took until 1987 for the trade deficit to start falling. This is because when a country&#39;s currency gets weaker, it takes years for exports to rise and imports to fall as a result. But what happens immediately is that imports get more expensive, which temporarily raise the trade deficit. These are called the “quantity effect” and the “valuation effect”. Eventually the quantity effect should overwhelm the valuation effect, but it takes time.</p></div></div> ;
How liberal democracy might lose the 21st centuryA scary little theory about information and freedom. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-lose https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-loseNoah Smith Wed, 22 May 2024 21:49:31 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg" width="1200" height="578" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:578,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:83339,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba726358-dce3-4784-82a3-5c71fbb1ca03_1200x578.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p> I was raised in an age of liberal triumphalism. Liberal democracy won the 20th century — imperialism, fascism, and communism all collapsed, and by the end of the century the US and its democratic allies in Asia and Europe were both economically and militarily ascendant. Even China, which remained an autocracy, liberalized its economy and parts of its society during this time. Even scholars who turned up their noses at Francis Fukuyama&#39;s “end of history” were generally favorable to arguments that capitalism and/or liberal democracy fostered <a href="https://pages.ucsd.edu/~egartzke/publications/gartzke_ajps_07.pdf">peace</a> , <a href="https://www.bu.edu/sthacker/files/2012/01/Democracy-and-Human-Development.pdf">happiness</a> , and <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-5907.2007.00299.x">prosperity</a> . There was an overwhelming sense that freedom — the freedom to speak your mind, to live as you liked, to buy and sell what you wished — was <em>the thing that won</em> .</p><p> Just two decades later, that idea is deeply in doubt. The wave of democratization and social liberalization <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-darkness">went into reverse</a> . The US has been riven by social and political chaos, and its weaknesses in manufacturing and homebuilding have been starkly exposed. Meanwhile China, the <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/china-at-the-peak">ascendant superpower</a> of the early 21st century, has <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/graphics/2024-governing-china-after-the-boom/?sref=R8NfLgwS">moved back toward</a> a more dirigiste economy and a more totalitarian society under Xi Jinping.</p><p>我认识的一些最近去中国旅游的人回来后都对中国与美国相比有多么美好的幻想： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg" width="656" height="839" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:839,&quot;width&quot;:656,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:245111,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F598ab4db-2e5a-4850-b29a-9511471f7c8e_656x839.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg" width="656" height="508.8665207877462" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:709,&quot;width&quot;:914,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:656,&quot;bytes&quot;:143163,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2480d36a-0801-444d-92d2-a35ae259552f_914x709.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>现在，我们不要得意忘形。 The asylum seekers <a href="https://www.wilsoncenter.org/article/through-darien-gap-new-path-chinese-asylum-seekers-united-states">fleeing China for the US</a> might disagree, as would many <a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2023/06/-china-pessimism-economy-censorship/674556/">regular Chinese people</a> whose nest eggs have been destroyed by the real estate bust. Glittering new shopping malls and train stations might simply be at the beginning of their capital depreciation cycle. Chinese apps and gadgets might simply be a case of technological leapfrogging that will eventually be leapfrogged in turn. High-speed rail might turn out to be a waste of resources in many areas. It&#39;s important to remember that China is only about <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_GDP_(PPP)_per_capita">30% as rich as the US</a> , even by the most optimistic measures.</p><p> And yet there&#39;s no doubt that China&#39;s cities <em>are</em> much cleaner and safer than San Francisco or NYC. Meanwhile, China can make electric vehicles, batteries, and computer chips galore, while <a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-build-nothing-country">it has yet to be shown</a> that America can do the same. China can provide plentiful housing to its people (sometimes <em>too</em> plentiful), while America struggles with chronic housing shortages. China is beating the US handily in terms of <a href="https://www.nathanielbullard.com/presentations">switching to green energy</a> . Nor is China&#39;s strength limited to manufacturing — TikTok is so well-made and addictive that it has outcompeted homegrown American short video services in their home market.</p><p> And despite the US&#39; well-documented difficulties, its liberal democratic allies are in <a href="https://x.com/Noahpinion/status/1793146797734666562">an even worse condition</a> .同时，中国正在建立一个强大的盟友网络 - 俄罗斯，伊朗和朝鲜 - 付出了付出的想法，即独裁者无法合作，并组建了一个可能已经<a href="https://www.slowboring.com/p/the-economics-of-the-new-cold-war">在军事上已经超越西方的</a>联盟。尽管得出关于政治政权的结论还为时过早，但尽管<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-positive-case-for-joe-biden">拜登的许多成功</a>与习近平的统治的稳定相反，但特朗普的可能返回可能还为时过早，尽管<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/what-if-xi-jinping-isnt-that-competent">他的统治有许多失误</a>。</p><p>中国尚未证明其系统的优势，但其成功提出了一个不舒服的问题：<em>这能否获胜？</em> Can <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-two-faces-of-chinas-surveillance-state-11662130940">universal surveillance</a> , speech control, suppression of <a href="https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/china-xinjiang-uyghurs-muslims-repression-genocide-human-rights">religion and minorities</a> , and economic command and control really be the keys to national power and stability in the 21st century?当这些事情在20日如此全面失败时，这怎么可能是真的？</p><p>我不知道。但这很有用，并考虑如何以及为什么对21世纪的世界<em>有</em>充分的适应性。实际上，我有一个理论，说明这是如何真实的。这个理论只是一个猜想 - 这是我不相信的事情，但我还不能说服自己是错误的。这是<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-super-scary-theory-of-the-21st-a3a">我之前写过的</a>一些东西的完善和扩展，但是随着时间的流逝，我开始以更连贯的形式将这些想法融合在一起。</p><p> So here you go: a theory of how totalitarianism might naturally triumph. The basic idea is that when information is costly, liberal democracy wins because it gathers more and better information than closed societies, but when information is cheap, negative-sum <em>information tournaments</em> sap an increasingly large portion of a liberal society&#39;s resources. Remember that I don&#39;t <em>believe</em> this theory; I&#39;m merely trying to formulate it.</p><h4>自由民主作为信息汇总者</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-lose">阅读更多</a></p>; 
In which British writers scold America on tradeIf you don't acknowledge the point of tariffs, how can you hope to criticize them? https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/in-which-which-british-writers-scold-america https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/in-which-which-british-writers-scold-americaNoah Smith Tue, 21 May 2024 10:07:17 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4a4b-b408-1ac24685909b_1174x548.jpeg" width="718" height="335.14821124361157" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4eb2f2c9-9fa2-4